cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with virtual network functions and their sharing in mobile networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the allocation of resources in a distributed system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing system performance while minimizing cost. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could be relevant as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to sharing VNFs among multiple services. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to meet the target KPIs of all services while minimizing cost.
